      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;this-craft-is-mine&#34;&gt;This Craft Is Mine&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;I looked at the level.dat&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;python3 -c &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;from nbt.nbt import NBTFile; f=NBTFile(&amp;#39;level.dat&amp;#39;); print(f.pretty_tree())&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;→ Didnt find anything relevant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Looked through the stats and found a .json file&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;thiscraft1.webp&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://batamladen.github.io/Dead-Pirate-Society/images/material/thiscraft1.webp&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here we see that blocks were placed, maybe we could find where they were placed. The suspicious blocks were white concrete and black concrete. To do that I used uNmINed, go to the Highlighters tab and click the + button, then entered the id: minecraft:black_concrete&lt;/p&gt;</description>
